        <ui:Label tabindex="-1" text="This project aims to try and make the generation of 3D models using the 3D Gaussian Splatting method more accessible and easy to use. We are not the authors of the method nor the 3D model viewer implementation in Unity, we merely strive to wrap the model generation and viewing within one simple program.&#10;The original method has been developed by Bernhard Kerbl, Georgios Kopanas, Thomas Leimkühler and George Drettakis in their paper &quot;3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering&quot; published in the ACM Transaction on Graphics in July of 2023.&#10;The Unity model viewer for Gaussian Splatting point clouds has been made by Aras Pranckevičius (aras-p on GitHub) as a fork of the original GitHub repository.&#10;The camera controller used is a slight modification of Freya Holmér&apos;s (FreyaHolmer on GitHub) FlyCamera controller she has shared on her GitHub.&#10;&#10;This program&apos;s authors are Bartosz Moczkowski, Filip Chmiel, Kamil Bartos, Juliusz Ciążyński and Magdalenna Bissinger. It was made as a project for the subject &quot;Process Modelling for Industry 4.0&quot; under the supervision of prof. Grzegorz Liśkiewicz." parse-escape-sequences="true" display-tooltip-when-elided="true" style="white-space: normal;" />
    </ui:VisualElement>
